   =20
      Risk
   =20
 =20
I just want to save this here for later:Credit Suisse is once again prepari=
ng to take on riskier business after a series of high-profile crises had pr=
ompted the bank to adopt a more cautious approach, according to the Swiss l=
ender=E2=80=99s new chief risk officer.David Wildermuth, who joined from Go=
ldman Sachs in January, said the bank was =E2=80=9Cmoving the pendulum back=
 the other way=E2=80=9D after ditching risker clients following the =E2=80=
=9Ccatastrophic events=E2=80=9D the business suffered last year.=E2=80=9CIt=
=E2=80=99s the second time in my career I feel I=E2=80=99m as much a cheerl=
eader for taking on more risk as I am for reducing risk =E2=80=94 the other=
 time was right after the financial crisis,=E2=80=9D he told investors at a=
n event on Tuesday.=E2=80=9CAs I=E2=80=99m going out and meeting with clien=
ts and our teams, I think we do want to take smart risk, where we really un=
derstand the risk, we are aware of the risk and we understand detailed outc=
omes of the risk,=E2=80=9D he added.If Credit Suisse Group AG has another  =
Archegos or  Greensill in the next year or so, let=E2=80=99s come back and =
make fun of David Wildermuth for saying this in public. Then the narrative =
will be =E2=80=9Cwe took some dumb risks and lost money on Archegos and Gre=
ensill, so we cleaned up our act and hired a new chief risk officer, who to=
ld us to take more risk, and, well, I guess we should have seen this coming=
.=E2=80=9DIf there are no big scandals for a while, though, let=E2=80=99s c=
ome back and congratulate him. =E2=80=9CTake more but smarter risks when ev=
eryone is fearful=E2=80=9D is kind of a reasonable approach, no?Really ther=
e are two jobs for a chief risk officer:=09Properly measure and calibrate r=
isk, helping the bank understand how to take smart risks in a way that safe=
ly maximizes expected value.=09Look very stern and serious and assure regul=
ators and the public that, what, no, we=E2=80=99re not taking any=C2=A0risk=
s=C2=A0around here.These jobs are in tension with each other, but one way t=
o manage that tension is to be appropriately commercial internally but not =
talk about it at public events? Trotting out your chief risk officer to tel=
l clients =E2=80=9Choo boy are we gonna take a ton of risk=E2=80=9D is just=
 an odd choice.=C2=A0
